---
name: external-review
description: "Run an external review tool and write findings to QA.md."
---

Run an external code review tool to review all changes on the current branch.

## Instructions

1. Verify the external review tool is available.
2. Run the review tool against all changes on the current branch compared to `<%= mainBranch %>`.
3. Format the findings into `QA.md` with severity tags:
   - `[critical]` — must fix before merge
   - `[warning]` — should fix, may defer with justification
   - `[suggestion]` — nice to have, can skip
4. Print a summary: total findings by severity, top 3 most important issues.

## Output

Write findings to `QA.md` in the repository root with this format:

```markdown
# QA Review

_Generated by external review tool on YYYY-MM-DD_

> **Note**: These findings are automated and may be inaccurate. Always verify before applying fixes.

## Findings

- [ ] [severity] **Title** — Description. File: `path/to/file.ts:line`
```

## Rules

- NEVER commit or push.
- Include a disclaimer that automated findings may be inaccurate.
